Ellen Crislip, 252 Operations Supervisor, contacted Safety regarding a UN1760 spill to the dock floor. Ellen Crislip advised Safety that while Steve Looney, dock worker, was unloading the freight one box was punctured by the forklift. Ellen Crislip stated a piece of the wood on the pallet broke caus ing the box to fall below the pallet resulting in the box being punctured. Ellen Crislip advised they placed pads down to soak the spill and the box is now upright not leaking. Ellen Crislip stated the dock worker was attempting to clean the spill in house. Safety directed Ellen Crislip to stop the dock worker. Safety stated Cura would need to be contacted for remediation. Ellen Crislip advised Cura to be contacted on straight time since the spill is contained. ~

There was NO RELEASE. The shipment is being held for FAA investigation.

column169: Cameron Logan Supervisor called safety to report a spill of UN1263, PAINT, 3, PG II. Cameron stated while the forklift operator was loading the pallet of paint, one of the 5-gallon pails on the pallet struck other fright in the trailer puncturing the bottom of one pail on the pallet the forklift was  loading. Cameron stated the forklift operator turned the pail on to its top to stop the spill and removed the pallet from the trailer to the dock floor and reported the spill. Cameron stated it looked like the spilled on the trailer floor has dried up and can no longer see where it spilled, and the  pallet has dried up as well showing no signs of a spill. Cameron stated it looks like 5oz may have spilled from the pail on the trailer floor and the pallet. Cameron stated he changed out the pallet with the spill with a new pallet for the other 3 pails and placed the damaged pail on the pallet wit h the spill. Cameron stated the spill on the trailer floor and on the pallet has dried and you can no longer see where the spill was and wanted to know what to do with the damaged pail. Safety advised CURA would be called to assist with the spill and the damaged pail.
column170: Refresher training on operating a forklift while loading and unloading freight.

column169: On 9/6/2024 at approximately 1115, Dangerous Goods Administration received a call from Employee 3962724 at the sort facility in Aguadilla, Puerto Rico, reporting undeclared dangerous goods.  The shipment consisted of several packages appearing to be processed through Amazon.   Spillage occurred among the packages, prompting FedEx to further investigate, resulting in the identification of the spilled package as nail polish remover, which was not prepared in accordance with IATA Regulations, missing the required markings, labeling, packaging and paperwork.  Dangerous Goods Administration obtained the safety data sheet of a similar product to verify indentification.   The other packages remain unopened and the contents unknown.   The spilled package was removed from the box and the remainder of the shipment is being held for package retreival.
